{
  "texts": [
    "The experimental results demonstrated that the suggested model could significantly increase the predictive accuracy of student accomplishments, and reaching up to 70.8%.",
    "Similarly, a student accomplishment prediction model based on evolving spiking neural networks was proposed in another study by Liu et al (2022b), based on a thorough analysis of the correlation between student and course features.",
    "The evolving membrane algorithm was added to train the model's hyperparameters, thereby enhancing the model's capability for prediction.",
    "Finally, using two benchmark student datasets (Alibaba Cloud Tianchi's xAPI-Edu-Data and the UCI machine learning library), the proposed model was employed to predict student achievement.",
    "The results of the experiment demonstrated that the model based on spiking neural networks can significantly increase the accuracy of predicting student achievement."
  ]
}